<pre class="bz_comment_text">(In reply to <a href="show_bug.cgi?id=614608#c4">comment #4</a>)
<span class="quote">&gt; I don't know what SUSE has done to approach upstream regarding it.</span >

I'm trying to figure that out. I told the SUSE maintainer to report the bug upstream but so far nothing has happened.

<span class="quote">&gt; I'm considering at a vulnerability because I'm of the frame of mind
&gt; that if you are hibernating or suspending your system, it is reasonable to
&gt; expect to be prompted for a password when you return to it.</span >

What makes you think so? Only because it is that way in GNOME?

